Switch statement 

Switch statments are used when the flow of the program is based on something other than boolean

----> Switch statements will be based on controlling expression
Controling expression can be byte, short, char, int and Strings
Keywords: switch , case

Syntax:

switch( Controlling_Expression){
	
	// your code here 
	case Case_Label:
}

--Case Lable should match the datatype of your controling expression
--you can have any number of cases 
The break keyword
This statment terminate(exit) the switch statement
you dont need to have a break, its optional .
--The default case is optional 

int a = 0;
switch(a){
	case 0:

	// statement for 0
	case 1:
	// statment for 1
}
